  "text": "The Kubernetes pod eviction on node memory pressure is implemented through a comprehensive system of threshold monitoring and decision logic located primarily in the eviction package.\n\nMemory pressure eviction thresholds are defined in platform-specific files:\n- Linux uses 100Mi as the default hard eviction threshold for memory.available (pkg/kubelet/eviction/defaults_linux.go)\n- Windows uses 500Mi as the default hard eviction threshold due to higher system process memory requirements (pkg/kubelet/eviction/defaults_windows.go)\n- Other platforms default to 100Mi (pkg/kubelet/eviction/defaults_others.go)\n\nThese thresholds are configured through the KubeletConfiguration via EvictionHard and EvictionSoft maps in pkg/kubelet/apis/config/types.go.\n\nThe eviction manager's decision logic is implemented in the synchronize() function in pkg/kubelet/eviction/eviction_manager.go, which is the main control loop that runs continuously to monitor and enforce eviction thresholds. The synchronize() function:\n1. Collects memory observations using makeSignalObservations() from pkg/kubelet/eviction/helpers.go\n2. Checks if thresholds are met using thresholdsMet() which compares current available memory against configured threshold values\n3. Determines node conditions (specifically NodeMemoryPressure) using nodeConditions() helper\n4. Ranks pods for eviction using rankMemoryPressure() which prioritizes pods by whether their memory usage exceeds requests, then by priority level\n5. Evicts pods starting with the highest priority candidates\n\nThe threshold system uses the evictionapi package (pkg/kubelet/eviction/api/types.go) which defines:\n- Signal types: SignalMemoryAvailable (capacity - workingSet) and SignalAllocatableMemoryAvailable\n- ThresholdOperator: OpLessThan (eviction occurs when available < threshold)\n- Threshold struct: Contains Signal, Operator, Value (absolute or percentage), GracePeriod, and MinReclaim\n\nKey functions in the decision chain:\n- ParseThresholdConfig() parses and validates threshold configuration from kubelet flags\n- isHardEvictionThreshold() identifies thresholds with zero grace period (immediate eviction)\n- The thresholdsMet() function performs the core comparison: if threshold.Operator is OpLessThan, eviction triggers when available resources are less than the threshold value\n- Pod ranking in rankMemoryPressure() sorts pods to evict BestEffort pods first, then Burstable pods exceeding requests, then Guaranteed pods\n\nThe IsUnderMemoryPressure() method returns the current state of memory pressure for node status reporting, which is determined during synchronize() by tracking NodeMemoryPressure conditions."
}

